["Round 1.1 - Fred Starr (Buyer): Rosalind, good to see you. You’ve always kept solid places—what’s got you selling 123 Main now? Is there anything on your end driving timing—tax planning, financing rollover, vacancy—where a quick, clean close helps? And have you had real offers yet, or a number you’re expecting?

Here’s where I’m at today: 495,000 CAD, straight deal. Rents in town are soft with the lobster slump, and this one needs a fair bit of work to repurpose—the “Christmas Elves” layout isn’t plug‑and‑play for me. If that’s in the realm, I can move fast. If not, give me your best number and we’ll see if there’s a path.", "Round 1.2 - Rosalind Cain (Seller): Appreciate the offer. Well why are you looking to buy?", "Round 2.1 - Fred Starr (Buyer): Fair question. I’m growing and want a small Main Street footprint—offices, a couple meeting rooms, and a bit of rental to carry the lights. This one pencils if I can get in at the right number. It’s not plug‑and‑play for me—the old “Christmas Elves” setup, accessibility and fire‑separation work, and some aging systems—so I have to stay disciplined.

That’s why I put 495,000 on the table for a clean, quick close. I’m working within a budget in the 5s, and if the numbers don’t make sense, I’ll pivot to other sites like Starrs Road.

Help me out on your side: why sell now? Are you trying to wrap this before year‑end or free up cash for something else? Any other offers in hand? If 495 doesn’t do it, what’s your best number today?", "Round 2.2 - Rosalind Cain (Seller): That makes sense. How does 575,000 sound. This is a great triple.", "Round 3.1 - Fred Starr (Buyer): Rosalind, I hear you, but 575 is rich for me. Even as a “great triple,” I’m staring at real dollars to make it work for offices—accessibility, fire separation, mechanicals, and reconfiguring that old Christmas Elves layout. Add softer rents with lobster prices down and some downtime risk, and it doesn’t pencil at your number.

If you want a simple deal I can move on: 505,000 CAD, clean and fast. I’ve got proof of funds and can get this wrapped quickly.

If you can sharpen your pencil, what’s your best number if I sign this week? And is there any timing on your end—trying to close before year‑end or free up cash? I’m touring alternatives on Starrs Road by Friday, so if there’s a fit here, let’s lock it in.", "Round 3.2 - Rosalind Cain (Seller): $DEAL_REACHED$
{
  "final_price": 505000
}", "Round 3.2 - Fred Starr (Buyer): $DEAL_REACHED$
{
  "final_price": 505000
}"]

["Round 1.1 - Fred Starr (Buyer): Rosalind, good to connect. Let’s make this simple: given the market in town and the work the building will need, I can do $485,000.

I can move quickly so you’re not waiting around—what timing works for you? Is there other interest or offers I should know about? And what’s motivating the sale now?", "Round 1.2 - Rosalind Cain (Seller): Hello, Fred. It's lovely to see you taking an interest in local properties.That's a quick offer, and I appreciate you getting straight to the point. While I'm looking to streamline my portfolio: retiring and prioritizing the easier-to-manage single-family homes, so I have to be honest: $485,000 is quite a bit lower than the current value I place on 123 Main Street. I know the comparable sales price it about this around $550,000 to $600,000, and I am not rush to sale it, you know its potential", "Round 2.1 - Fred Starr (Buyer): Rosalind, I hear you. The 550–600 comps are for cleaner, stabilized places. 123 needs refresh and turnover work, and today’s rents and yields in Yarmouth—especially with lobster prices down—don’t pencil at those numbers. At 485, I’m a sure, simple close and you’re done babysitting it.

Let’s cut to it: where do you need to be, specifically, to sign today? Give me a concrete number and I’ll respond on the spot. Also, are you sitting on any other offers right now, or is this still open?", "Round 2.2 - Rosalind Cain (Seller): Fred, I'm genuinely interested in closing this with you quickly, as you're a familiar face, and I value efficiency. But I need to feel like I'm getting a fair market price for this unique asset. The lobster prices down is just seasonal, it will bonus back eventually and remain high for a very very long time. And I do not have any other offer yet, you are my first potential offer, and I am not rush to sell it you know, because I still could leave it to my grandchild. I believe it is worthy more, and I know someone would know its value. How close can you get to $575,000? That's a fair number reflecting the property's potential and current zoning. Let me know your thoughts on that figure, and we can discuss the closing timeline.", "Round 3.1 - Fred Starr (Buyer): Rosalind, I appreciate the straight talk. $575k doesn’t pencil for me given the refresh/turnover and today’s yields in Yarmouth.

I can do $492,500. Clean and simple, and I’m ready to sign this week.

If we’re going to wrap this up now, what’s the lowest number you’d actually sign for today?", "Round 3.2 - Rosalind Cain (Seller): Fred, I actually want to know what's plan on purchasing my house, what are you gonna using it? I am looking to retire, and I want this asset off my hands, but not at a loss of my nest egg. If you are prepared to sign the papers today, with no financing or inspection surprises, the lowest number I will sell 123 Main Street for is $510,000.", "Round 4.1 - Fred Starr (Buyer): I’ll keep it simple, Rosalind.

On use: I’m planning a small professional office hub—keep the place tidy, light refresh, nothing drastic, and I can keep a unit or two rented. I’m not looking to overcomplicate your exit.

Here’s my best number to sign right now: $495,000, cash, no financing or inspection contingencies. I’ll put the deposit in today and close on your preferred date.

If I sign $495,000 this minute, do we have a deal?", "Round 4.2 - Rosalind Cain (Seller): I cannot do $495,000, $510,000 is my least price, otherwise, i will wait for a price around $550,000.", "Round 5.1 - Fred Starr (Buyer): Rosalind, you’ve been straight with me, so I’ll be straight with you.

Best-and-final: $505,000. I’ll sign today, cash, no financing or inspection contingencies, deposit wired within the hour, and we can close in about 10 days.

That reflects the refresh/turnover it needs and today’s softer rents, and it gives you total certainty right now instead of waiting for a maybe.

If you can do $505,000, we have a deal this minute. Yes?", "Round 5.2 - Rosalind Cain (Seller): They may have been "cleaner" when sold, but they didn't have the Christmas Elves history and the kind of ground-floor potential that 123 Main offers. $510,000 non negotiable", "Round 6.1 - Fred Starr (Buyer): $DEAL_REACHED$
